-- Ulster Defeats Edinburgh 22-19 to Reach Heineken Cup Rugby Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-04-28T19:09:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/ulster-defeats-edinburgh-22-19-to-reach-heineken-cup-rugby-final.html
Ulster defeated Edinburgh 22-19 to
advance to the Heineken Cup rugby final for the first time in 13
years.  Ruan Pienaar kicked 17 points to lead Ulster to the home
win in Dublin. Pienaar booted five penalties and converted
Pedrie Wannenburg’s first-half try.  Greg Laidlaw kicked 14 points and James Thompson touched
down for Edinburgh, the first Scottish team to reach the
semifinals of  Europe ’s top club competition.  Ulster will meet Clermont Auvergne or Leinster, who play
tomorrow, for the title May 19 at Twickenham Stadium in  London .
Ulster defeated Colomiers 21-6 in its previous final appearance
in 1999.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
